Description
===========
Crashinfo is an utility designed to collect information about a crashing
process. These information are collected from /proc and from the core file,
which is read from the standard input, which makes crashinfo suitable for
being installed in /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern.

Installation
============
Adapt "Configuration" section of Makefile (or pass related options trough
environment variables) and run the usual:
  make
  make install
which install the "coreinfo" binary.
